{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a847c222-7f7d-4ee9-a3de-5bcf6c534eba","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so here's what you can do:\n\n### Analyze with `dotnet-dump`\n```bash\n# Install the tool if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Open the dump interactively\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nOnce inside, useful commands:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Show last exception details |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for OOM issues) |\n| `setthread <id>` | Switch threads |\n\n### Quick start sequence\n```\n> pe              # Check for an unhandled exception\n> clrthreads      # Find faulting thread\n> setthread <id>  # Switch to it\n> clrstack        # See what it was doing\n```\n\n### Alternatives\n- **Visual Studio** — File → Open → File, then select the `.dmp`; click \"Debug with Managed Only\"\n- **lldb** (Linux/macOS) — load with the SOS plugin via `dotnet-sos install`\n\nWould you like help with any specific step or error you're seeing during analysis?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8e6ad3c2-fe58-4ad8-b8da-c945f800d377","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description says it's for collecting/configuring crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. It explicitly states \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":454,"requestId":"7850:36C8E1:2090C9F:241DF2E:69FA9F2B"},"id":"bd67e8f9-396d-41ac-b80b-2f172e7aabf3","timestamp":"202